==English==

===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1891|1891]], from [[alcohol]] + [[-ic]]

===Noun===
'''alcoholic'' (''plural:'' '''[[alcoholics]]''')
# a person addicted to [[alcohol]]
# one who abuses alcohol

====Antonyms====
* [[teetotal]]

====Translations====
*Chinese: [[酒客]] (jiǔ kè)
*Finnish: [[alkoholisti]]
*German:  [[Alkoholiker]]
*Latvian: [[alkoholiķis]] ''m''
*[[Persian]]: [[الکلی]] (alkoli)
*Polish: [[alkoholik]] ''m'', [[alkoholiczka]] ''f''
*Russian: [[алкоголик]] (alkogoljik) ''m''
*Slovak:  [[alkoholik]] ''m'' (alkoholici ''pl'') (1), [[pijan]] ''m'' (2)
*Swedish: [[alkoholist]] ''c'' (1,2)

===Adjective===
'''alcoholic'''
# of or pertaining to alcohol
# having more than a trace amount of alcohol in its contents
#: ''alcoholic beverage''

====Antonyms====
* [[nonalcoholic]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[alkoholi-]] (1), [[alkoholipitoinen]] (2)
*Latvian: [[alkoholisks]] (1,2)
*Polish: [[alkoholowy]] ''m''
*Slovak: [[alkoholický]] ''m'', [[alkoholická]] ''f'', [[alkoholické]] ''n''
*Swedish: [[alkohol-]] (1), [[alkoholhaltig]] (2)

===Related terms===
* [[alcohol]]

===See also===
* [[alcoholic beverage]]
* [[-holic]]

